Integration Tests

Purpose: Tests that verify multiple units working together, including real database access and HTTP request/response cycles.

What belongs here:
- Endpoint integration tests (POST /api/v1/Auth/Login, GET /api/v1/User, etc.)
- Database integration tests with a test database instance
- WebBroker request/response pipeline tests
- Transaction rollback and commit scenario tests
- Authentication flow end-to-end tests
- Concurrent request handling tests

Test framework: DUnitX (recommended) with a dedicated test database.
Each test should set up and tear down its own test data.
Tests may require a running TIdHTTPWebBrokerBridge instance on a test port.

